com.bigdata.rdf.sparql.ast

Class BSBMQ5Setup

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bigdata.rdf.sparql.ast.BSBMQ5Setup

  • public class BSBMQ5Setup
extends Object
    Problem setup for BSBM Q5.

    Analysis of BSBM Q5

    The following predicates all join on #product:

    • p0
    • p2
    • p4
    • p5
    The predicates (p3 and p5) do not directly join with any of the other predicates (they do not directly share any variables). In general, a join without shared variables means the cross product of the sources will be materialized and such joins should be run last.

    However, in this case there are two SPARQL FILTERs ( c1 and c2) which (a) use those variables (BSBMQ5Setup#origProperty1 and BSBMQ5Setup#origProperty2); and (b) can constrain the query. This means that running the predicates without shared variables and applying the constraints before the tail of the plan can in fact lead to a more efficient join path.
